  "prompt": "What are the best free WordPress plugins in 2014?",
  "response": "In 2014, several free WordPress plugins stood out for their functionality and popularity among users. Here are some of the best free WordPress plugins from that year:\n\n1. **Yoast SEO**: This plugin became a staple for optimizing websites for search engines. It provided tools for SEO analysis, XML sitemap generation, and readability checks.\n\n2. **Jetpack by WordPress.com**: Jetpack offered a suite of features including site stats, social sharing, security enhancements, and more, making it a versatile choice for many WordPress users.\n\n3. **Contact Form 7**: A simple yet powerful plugin for creating and managing contact forms. It allowed users to customize forms and manage submissions easily.\n\n4. **WooCommerce**: Although more than just a plugin, the WooCommerce plugin enabled users to turn their WordPress sites into fully functional eCommerce stores.\n\n5. **Wordfence Security**: A popular security plugin that provided firewall protection, malware scanning, and login security features to help protect WordPress sites.\n\n6. **Akismet**: This plugin helped filter out spam comments, making it easier for site owners to manage and maintain their comment sections.\n\n7. **W3 Total Cache**: A performance optimization plugin that helped improve site speed through caching, which is crucial for user experience and SEO.\n\n8. **Gravity Forms**: Although primarily a premium plugin, Gravity Forms had a free version that provided basic form-building capabilities, which were very useful for many users.\n\n9. **Duplicate Post**: This plugin allowed users to clone posts and pages easily, which was helpful for those who wanted to maintain consistency across similar content.\n\n10. **NextGEN Gallery**: This plugin provided robust gallery management features, allowing users to create and manage image galleries effectively.\n\nThese plugins were widely used and recommended in 2014 for their reliability and the value they added to WordPress sites. Many of them continue to be popular choices today.",
